cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CG, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with maintaining a DFS tree in a dynamic environment, which is a problem related to data structures and graph algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category. The paper also presents results related to graph theory, such as subgraph connectivity and biconnectivity, which suggest that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are also likely categories. The paper involves computational geometry, as it deals with maintaining a DFS tree in an undirected graph, which can be represented as a geometric object. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a possible category. Finally, the paper presents worst-case time complexity results, which suggest that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as well.
